snippet.textDisplay:
Are you trying to convey political messages with the prints on the characters' shirts?
"Black Planet" meaning, this planet rightfully only belongs to people of colour.
Or "It's Not Rael" meaning it is actually Palestine and not Israel.

If I hit the nail on the head with my suspicions, I have to say you are getting worse and worse. Which is so painful, since I once considered you to be the best musical artists in the world, especially when Demon Dayz came out - such a great album. Compared to that, most of your recent work is garbage, that seems to serve a political agenda.
This is so weak.

Please go back to how you were back in the days, before the disaster of Humanz, which was mainly a pathetic collection of pc bvllsh!t.
